I first did `export default Tagify;`, but the "CI / test" failed with the reason `NoDefaultExports`. That's why I changed it, after some research and local testing, to `export =`.

So, how to address default exports, such that DefinitelyTyped checks will be happy?

In this earlier version, I also exported the interfaces next to the default export:

```typescript
export interface TagifySettings { }
export interface TagData { }
export default class Tagify { }

// "CI / test" failed with NoDefaultExports
```

